Hi,

That is a very good point.
Rote learning would work up until you encounter a word which wasn&#39;t (or
was spelled differently) in your dictionary.

I&#39;ve heard that sign languages are pretty independent of written/spoken
languages anyway, so a change of alphabet wouldn&#39;t affect them.
It seems to me (and this is only my opinion since I really have no right
to say one way or the other) that someone who&#39;s everyday language was a
sign language would prefer a system like SignWriting
&lt;http://www.signwriting.org/&gt; for their written materials anyway.

Braille has a near direct mapping with roman letters so a new system
would be needed, any thoughts?

